CausationThis is intended to be a very general schema that specifies a causal relation between two situations (a 'cause' and an 'effect'). Perhaps prototypically, cause and effect occur as part of a scenario in which the 'process' (casual_process) associated with one entity (the causer) is conceptualized as somehow affecting the process (affected_process) associated with another entity (affected). This very general frame is meant to encompass many different types of causes (including, e.g., both force-application and the lack thereof), different types of 'causal' relations (e.g. cause, prevent, enable, help, hinder), and different types of 'affected processes' (including, e.g., the motion, location, or state of the affected entity).Causationcause.v
